  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.validation.base.ObjectValidatorBuilder<V,PARENT,SELF>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the generic type of the value to validate.
    PARENT - the generic type of the parent builder.
    SELF - the generic type of this builder itself (this).
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<AbstractValidator<? super V>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:

    public abstract class ObjectValidatorBuilder<V,PARENT,SELF extends ObjectValidatorBuilder<V,PARENT,SELF>>
extends Object
implements Builder<AbstractValidator<? super V>>
    This is the base class to create instances of AbstractValidator using the builder pattern.

      • range

        public abstract SELF range(String min,
                           String max)
        This method allows to define a range in a generic way. If you have a properly typed builder please use more specific methods such as CompareableValidatorBuilder.range(net.sf.mmm.util.value.api.Range) instead.
        Parameters:
        min - the minimum value allowed or null for no lower bound.
        max - the maximum value allowed or null for no upper bound.
        Returns:
        this build instance for fluent API calls.
